Experiment 2: Build a College Website Header with Navbar, Tabs/Pills, and Alerts
‚Ä¢	Create a Navbar with brand name and menu items (Home, Departments, Contact).
‚Ä¢	Add a Tabs/Pills section below it to switch between content (Overview, Notices, Help).
‚Ä¢	Show Bootstrap Alerts inside the Notices tab (e.g., ‚ÄúAdmissions Open!‚Äù).
‚Ä¢	Analyze: Discuss when Tabs/Pills are better than separate pages.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>College Website</title>
  <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>

<!-- üîπ Navbar -->
